bution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Johannes ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hansel","meanings":["Pet form of   Johannes ."]}]},{"name":"Michael","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of a common biblical name (meaning ‘who is like God?’ in Hebrew) borne by one of the archangels, the protector of the ancient Hebrews, who is also regarded as a saint of the Catholic Church. In the Middle Ages, Michael was regarded as captain of the heavenly host (see Revelation 12:7–9), symbol of the Church Militant, and patron of soldiers. He was often depicted bearing a flaming sword. The name is also borne by a Persian prince and ally of Belshazzar mentioned in the Book of Daniel. Since the early 1900s it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names in the English-speaking world.  See also  Michal ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1353606,"age":3,"year":"1499","julianDay":2268559,"description":"Swiss forces defeated the forces of the Holy Roman Empire. Switzerland won its complete independence from the empire.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1353607,"age":40,"year":"1536","julianDay":2282072,"description":"Switzerland is a loose confederacy of 13 cities and small valley communities dominating the rest of the country. A few families control state affairs. Several rebellions put down by military force: repressed aspects of history in a country so proud of it's tradition of democracy.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Hans Michael Spilmann was born about 1496, in Zug, Zug, Switzerland, his father, Welti Spilmann, was 28 and his mother, Barbara Stadlin, was 26. He had at least 2 sons and 3 daughters with Margaretha Hess."},"et":{"abt1496–":"umbes 1496–Surnud","1496–Male":"1496–Surnud","1497–Female":"1497–Surnud","1498–Male":"1498–Surnud","1499–Male":"1499–Surnud","1500–Female":"1500–Surnud","1498–F